<br>
Sure a Bard can fear kite, charm 2 mobs...and pet can follow and attack the fleeing mob...<br>
<br>
My point is if they can do that, why would they need a mage?  The answer is they don't.  They can do this stuff all by their lonesome and thus actualy suffer by sharing xp with the mage...sure the battle ends a little sooner but there is a substansial risk that pets chasing mobs can aggro other creatures...<br>
<br>
Bard's have lots of great songs that are wonderful at bumping resistances, healing, and of course buffing and some debuffing of mobs...My point is that a good amount of this ability is wasted and inefficient in a Mage/Bard group.  Put them in a group with tanks and a wizard and they really shine.<br>
<br>
That is my point...The shaman and the mage complement each other very well and thus make hunting extremely efficient, which in turn reducess downtime and increases xp gain.  Moreso than almost any other combination IMHO.  <br>
<br>
Sure Mage/Mage and Mage/Necro can deal out a tremendous amount of damage...but neither are ideal pullers, escape is difficult, healing is marginal, downtime is pretty significant.  Good combination for taking out yellows and some reds in controlled spawn locations, but not general purpose. <p>Everwind Gale

Archmistlord of Magicians 
