<br>
Mage/Enchanter<br>
<br>
Mages are the best at killing 1 thing.  Any more and well, we have problems...so the enchanter saves our butt.<br>
<br>
Enchanters get decent slow spells, which reduces damage to pet a whole lot.<br>
<br>
And, that crappy enchanter pet that many high levels have stuck at the back of the book can come out to play again.<br>
<br>
Normally a battle vs a single mob goes like this.<br>
<br>
Earth pet (very important to keep the pet off the chanter) BO3, DS.  Enchanter pet gets a dagger and DS.<br>
<br>
Mage pulls with Malosi or similar, enchanter tashes, slows, dots and then whacks the mob with a pointed stick to get beaten a little, so their pet will attack.<br>
<br>
Mage nukes, enchanter casts Berserker Spirit on whichever pet is getting beaten on the most.<br>
<br>
I've found that with 2 of us we can take about 3-4 times the number of mobs that I can take soloing.<br>
<br>
Oh yeah, and Clarity =)<br>
<br>
If you group with an enchanter who uses a pet like this, you might want to make a /target &lt;enchanterpetname&gt; hotkey, as those little floating swords/daggers are notoriously difficult to target.<br>
<br>
